HEADWORD: Conformator
<hw>Con"for*ma`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
framer.]</ety> <def>An apparatus for taking the conformation of
anything, as of the head for fitting a hat, or, in craniometry, finding
the largest horizontal area of the head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

